Key names for common characters. These should be used with keyup/keydown events, since the .keyCode property on those is meant to indicate the

  • physical key* the user held down on the keyboard. Hence the mapping uses only the unshifted version of each key (e.g. no '#', since that's shift+3). Keypress events on the other hand generate (mostly) ASCII codes since they correspond to characters the user typed.

For further reference: http://unixpapa.com/js/key.html

This list is not localized and therefore some of the key codes are not correct for non-US keyboard layouts.
